article.description: China Threatt came off the bench and scored 16 points and Allie Quigley and Deirdre Naughton added 15 apiece to lead DePaul (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) in a 93-51 victory over Loyola of Chicago on Saturday night.
article.headline: Threatt scores 16 off bench as DePaul routs Loyola of Chicago
article.linkText: Threatt comes off bench to pace No. 16 DePaul
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- China Threatt came off the bench and scored 16 points and Allie Quigley and Deirdre Naughton added 15 apiece to lead DePaul (No. 16 ESPN/USA Today, No. 15 AP) in a 93-51 victory over Loyola of Chicago on Saturday night.

Erin Cattell chipped in 13 points and Natasha Williams added 12 points and had a game high 11 rebounds for the Blue Demons (7-0), who led 53-26 at the half.

DePaul shot 37-for-84 from the field, or 44 percent, compared with Loyola of Chicago's 20-for-55, or 36.4 percent.

Brittany Boeke, the only double-digit scorer for the Ramblers (1-8 ), had 13 points and five rebounds. Maggie McCloskey had five assists, and Jessica Hylton pulled down seven rebounds.

The game Saturday was the 40th time DePaul and Loyola have met. DePaul now leads the series leads 31-9.
